Definition.WordDefinition: dead end n 1: a passage with access only at one end [syn: {cul}, {cul de sac}] 2: a situation in which no progress can be made or no advancement is possible; "reached an impasse on the negotiations" [syn: {deadlock}, {impasse}, {stalemate}, {standstill}]
dead-end adj : lacking opportunities for development or advancement; "stuck in a dead-end job"
